<title>UK: Abbey and Willis Corroon to form IFA jv.</title>
<headline>Abbey and Willis Corroon to form IFA jv.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>British bank Abbey National Plc Plc and insurer Willis Corroon are to merge their independent financial advisor (IFA) operations to form a new business, the companies said in a joint statement.</p>
<p>The new company, to be called Willis National, will be owned 51 percent by Willis with the remainder held by Abbey National.</p>
<p>Willis National will buy Abbey National Independent Financial Advisors and Willis Corroon Financial Planning Ltd, with full integration expected by the end of the year.</p>
<p>--London Newsroom +44 171 542 4019</p>
